<br>
Aspen's comment is the key, I think, to the background story surrounding this movement: <br>
<br>
 &quot;Elves cannot be evil (other than those shifty rogues <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). We are beset on all sides by races that hold out the open hand, only to have the other fist crush down on us and our lands when we are not looking. Other races can be evil, so it is our duty remove the yoke of the ones that would hold us down.&quot; <br>
<br>
 If people are upset /ooc because they are having difficulty banking, and exp'ing in our zones, simply because they wish to keep the status-quo - I have no sympathy. Business as usual will not be the norm in the elven cities while we are there. <br>
<br>
 These folks who are all bent out of shape about it need to focus thier energies on the roleplaying aspects, and fighting for what they want (even though I disagree with what thier vision of the server is - I RESPECT THEIR RIGHT TO HAVE AND PURSUE THAT VISION), they will just have to fight for it from now on - instead of it being handed to them on a silver platter.  <p>Dorkmid 
